UID:10000801-1778335200-1778346000@unitedindians.org
SUMMARY:Artist Reception: "Anywhere But Here" by Mia Sutanto
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Sacred Circle Gallery Saturday May 9 2026 2 to 5 PM\nUnited Indians of All Tribes Foundation invites you to a special artist reception featuring Zuni Pueblo and Chinese Indonesian artist Mia Sutanto. Held in conjunction with our annual Mother’s Day Native Art Market this event offers a unique opportunity to meet the artist and experience her newest solo exhibition “Anywhere But Here” currently on view at the Daybreak Star Indian Cultural Center! \nAbout the Event\nThe reception will feature an artist talk and a chance to view Sutanto’s powerful 2 D digital art and paintings. Her work explores themes of femininity mixed cultural identity and mental health awareness. Through a striking use of the color red Sutanto explores how anger can be a transformative and healthy emotion while drawing attention to the strength of Indigenous women and the responsibility to protect ancestral lands. \nSpecial Announcement\nWe are thrilled to share that a signature piece from this exhibition will be the featured artwork for our  37th Annual Indian Days Powwow flyer. \nDetails\n\n\nWhere: Sacred Circle Gallery inside Daybreak Star Indian Cultural Center (Discovery Park) \n\n\nWhen: May 9\, 2026 (during the Mother’s Day Native Art Market) \n\n\nTime: 2 PM to 5 PM \n\n\nCost: Free and open to the public \n\n\nThe exhibition is curated by José E. Montaño (Aymara Quechua) an MTV Award winning director and curator who has led 20 solo exhibits at Sacred Circle Gallery since 2021.
URL:https://unitedindians.org/event/artist-reception-anywhere-but-here-by-mia-sutanto/
LOCATION:Daybreak Star Indian Cultural Center\, 5011 Bernie Whitebear Way\, Seattle\, WA\, 98199\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://unitedindians.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Mia-Sutanto-Banner-Proof.pdf-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
